# AI Service Rules

## Gemini API
- Initialize once in `lib/gemini.ts`
- Use `gemini-1.5-pro` for generation, `text-embedding-004` for embeddings
- Always set temperature, topP, maxOutputTokens explicitly
- Apply rate limiting on all Gemini calls
- Cache repeated generation results in Redis (TTL: 1h)

## Pinecone
- Initialize once in `lib/pinecone.ts`
- Index naming: `research-{environment}` (e.g. `research-production`)
- Always include metadata: `{ userId, documentId, chunkIndex, role }`
- Filter by `userId` or `departmentId` on every query — never return cross-user vectors
- Chunk size: 512 tokens, overlap: 50 tokens

## RAG Pipeline

// Standard RAG flow

1. extractText(file)           // pdf-parse or similar
2. chunkText(text, 512, 50)    // chunk with overlap
3. embedChunks(chunks)         // Gemini embeddings
4. upsertToPinecone(vectors)   // with metadata
5. queryPinecone(queryEmbed)   // top-K=5, filter by userId
6. buildPrompt(context, query) // system + retrieved chunks + question
7. generateResponse(prompt)    // Gemini
8. formatCitations(sources)    // map back to source docs


## LangChain
- Use for: complex chains, conditional flows, tool use
- Keep chain definitions in `features/ai/chains/`
- Log all chain inputs/outputs for debugging

## Async Processing
- Long AI operations (proposal gen, literature review) run as background jobs
- Use a queue (BullMQ + Redis) for batch AI operations
- Return a `jobId` immediately, poll for results
- Stream responses where possible using Vercel AI SDK streaming
